<subSubSection id="F1F9AEBB9C5B2A11EFC15E85FC2D5C7D" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" type="description">
<paragraph id="B95CFD309C5B2A11EFC15E85FF7F5DF3" blockId="35.[151,592,151,211]" box="[151,249,186,211]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
(
<figureCitation id="21D8E1B59C5B2A11EFC95E85FF765DF3" box="[159,240,186,211]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="36.[151,249,1973,1995]" captionTargetBox="[218,1349,207,1924]" captionTargetId="figure-47@36.[209,1361,193,1931]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURE 18. Megistopus flavicornis (Rossi, 1790), 3rd instar larva (Italy: Sardinia, Alghero). Dorsal (above), ventral (middle) and lateral (below) view; aâ€“g: diagnostic characters, see species description. (photo by C. Cesaroni)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4909429" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4909429/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B95CFD309C5B2A11EFC15EC2FC2D5C7D" blockId="35.[151,1436,253,1325]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
As the older reports actually refers to other species (
<bibRefCitation id="DD7280C19C5B2A11EDB95EC2FC505C36" author="Redtenbacher, J." box="[751,982,253,278]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="335 - 368" refId="ref41745" refString="Redtenbacher, J. (1884) Ubersicht der Myrmeleoniden-Larven. Denkschriften, Akademie der Wissenschaften Wien, Mathematische-Naturwissenschaftliche Klasse, 48, 335 - 368." type="journal article" year="1884">Redtenbacher, 1884</bibRefCitation>
), the first description of the larva of 
<taxonomicName id="7EE386B39C5B2A11EA2B5EC1FE895C1A" baseAuthorityName="Rossi" baseAuthorityYear="1790" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Megistopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavicornis">
<emphasis id="8B9721229C5B2A11EA2B5EC1FE895C1A" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">M. flavicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was realized by 
<bibRefCitation id="DD7280C19C5B2A11EE875F1EFDFE5C1A" author="Steffan, J. R." box="[465,632,289,314]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="693 - 707" refId="ref42381" refString="Steffan, J. R. (1965) Les larves de Megistopus flavicornis (Rossi), Creoleon lugduense (Villers), Neuroleon ocreatus (Navas) et N. nemausiensis (Borkh.) (Planipennes, Myrmeleontidae). Vie et Milieu, 15, 693 - 707." type="journal article" year="1965">Steffan (1965)</bibRefCitation>
. Later 
<bibRefCitation id="DD7280C19C5B2A11ED915F1EFC465C1A" author="Cesaroni, C. &amp; Nicoli Aldini, R. &amp; Pantaleoni, R. A." box="[711,960,289,314]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="135 - 144" refId="ref39087" refString="Cesaroni, C., Nicoli Aldini, R. &amp; Pantaleoni, R. A. (2010) The larvae of Gymnocnemia variegata (Schneider, 1845) and Megistopus flavicornis (Rossi, 1790) (Neuroptera: Myrmeleontidae): a comparative description. In: Devetak, D., Lipovsek, S., Arnett, A. E. (Eds.), Proceedings of the 10 th International Symposium on Neuropterology (22 - 25 June 2008, Piran, Slovenia). University of Maribor, Maribor, Slovenia, pp. 135 - 144." type="book chapter" year="2010">
Cesaroni 
<emphasis id="8B9721229C5B2A11EC655F1DFCEB5C1A" box="[819,877,289,314]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">et al.</emphasis>
(2010)
</bibRefCitation>
redescribed exhaustively the larva of this species comparing it with the closely related 
<taxonomicName id="7EE386B39C5B2A11EDD95F79FC225C7D" baseAuthorityName="Schneider" baseAuthorityYear="1845" box="[655,932,326,349]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Gymnocnemia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="variegata">
<emphasis id="8B9721229C5B2A11EDD95F79FC225C7D" box="[655,932,326,349]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Gymnocnemia variegata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
